---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 22, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  pathname="/en/terms"
  title="Automata — Terms of Use"
  description="The conditions under which this website is made available: permitted use, intellectual property, liability and governing law."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="section-index mb-8">
          <span>—</span>
          <span>Terms</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="h-display mb-6">
          Terms <em>of use</em>.
        </h1>
        <p class="t-lead mb-6 max-w-2xl">
          The minimum rules for using this site. Nothing surprising — but worth having in writing.
        </p>
        <p class="t-caption t-mono">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section pt-0">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-14">

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">01 — Who we are</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">The operator behind Automata.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              This website (<span class="t-mono">beautomata.com</span>) is operated by
              <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">AUTOMATA AI LLC</strong>,
              a limited liability company registered in the state of Kansas, United States.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Address: 17418 Jessica St, Gardner, Kansas 66030, USA</li>
              <li>EIN: 33-3383598</li>
              <li>Legal contact: <a href="mailto:legal@beautomata.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">legal@beautomata.com</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Below we use <em>"Automata"</em>, <em>"we"</em>, or <em>"our"</em> to refer to this entity, and
              <em>"you"</em> or <em>"user"</em> to refer to anyone accessing the site.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">02 — Acceptance</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Using the site means accepting these terms.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              By accessing or browsing <span class="t-mono">beautomata.com</span> you accept these terms and
              our <a href="/en/privacy" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">privacy policy</a>.
              If you disagree with any part, please do not use the site.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">03 — What this site is</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">An informational site, not a product.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              This site exists to present Automata's consulting and development services, publish case
              studies, and make it easy for you to contact us. It is not a platform, requires no sign-up,
              and offers no functionality beyond reading content and sending us an email.
            </p>
            <p>
              Any commercial relationship is formalized separately through a signed contract or proposal.
              Nothing on this site, by itself, constitutes a binding offer.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">04 — Intellectual property</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Our content is ours. Open source is everyone's.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              The text, design, images, <em>Automata</em> brand and other original content on this site are
              property of AUTOMATA AI LLC unless otherwise noted, and are protected by applicable intellectual
              property laws.
            </p>
            <p>
              You may read, print and share links to the content for personal or informational purposes. You
              may not reproduce, modify or use it commercially without our written consent.
            </p>
            <p>
              Open-source projects linked from this site (for example <span class="t-mono">orch-agents</span>)
              are governed by their own public licenses — primarily MIT. Those licenses override this section
              for the code in question.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">05 — Third-party links</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">We link, we don't control.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              This site may contain links to third-party sites (GitHub, articles, tools). We are not
              responsible for the content, privacy practices or availability of those sites. Accessing them
              is at your own risk.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">06 — No warranties</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">The site is offered "as is".</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the site and its content are provided
              <em>"as is"</em> and <em>"as available"</em>, without express or implied warranties of
              merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, or freedom from errors.
            </p>
            <p>
              We work to keep it running and up to date, but do not guarantee it will always be free of
              interruptions or errors.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">07 — Limitation of liability</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Liability, bounded.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              To the maximum extent permitted by law, AUTOMATA AI LLC will not be liable for indirect,
              incidental, special, consequential or punitive damages arising from your use or inability to
              use this site, including loss of data, revenue or profits.
            </p>
            <p>
              Nothing in these terms limits liability that, by law, cannot be limited (for example liability
              for willful misconduct, fraud, or injuries caused by gross negligence).
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">08 — Governing law and venue</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Kansas, United States.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Kansas, United States, without regard to
              its conflict-of-laws rules. Any dispute related to the site or to these terms shall be brought
              before the competent state or federal courts located in Johnson County, Kansas.
            </p>
            <p>
              The foregoing is without prejudice to any mandatory consumer rights you may have under the
              laws of your place of residence.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">09 — Changes</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Updates with a visible date.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              We may update these terms to reflect legal, technical or scope changes. The version in effect
              is always the one published on this page, dated at the top. Continued use of the site after an
              update means you accept the new version.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">10 — Contact</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Questions about these terms?</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              Email us at
              <a href="mailto:legal@beautomata.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">legal@beautomata.com</a>
              or by postal mail at the address listed in section 01.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
